HEADWORD: Housewifely
<hw>House"wife`ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining or
appropriate to a housewife; domestic; economical; prudent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A good sort of woman, ladylike and <qex>housewifely</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Housewifery</ent>⟦br⟧
